==Catalan==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|ca}} {{term|stare|stāre|stand|lang=la}}, present active infinitive of {{term|sto|stō|stand|lang=la}}

===Verb===
{{ca-verb|ar-irr|est|pres_1_sg=estic}}

# {{transitive|copular|lang=ca}} to [[currently]] [[be]] in a [[state]] or have a [[characteristic]] {{gloss|Used to connect a noun to an adjective that describes a temporary state of being.}}
#: '''''Estic''' cansada.''
#:: I '''am''' tired.
# {{auxiliary|lang=ca}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to form the [[continuous]] [[aspect]], together with a [[present participle]].}}
#: ''Ja '''està''' dormint.''
#:: He '''is''' already sleeping.
# {{intransitive|+adverbial phrase|lang=ca}} To be [[located]] {{gloss|to be in a place}}
#: ''La Torre Eiffel '''està''' a París.''
#:: The Eiffel Tower '''is''' in Paris.

====Usage notes====
This is one of two verbs that can be translated as ''to be'', the other being {{term|ser|lang=ca}}/{{term|ésser|lang=ca}}. ''Ser/ésser'' indicates something that is inherent and not expected to change, whereas ''estar'' describes temporary qualities that apply only at a particular time. ''Ser/ésser'' relates to ''estar'' as {{term|essence|lang=en}} relates to {{term|state|lang=en}}, etymologically as well as semantically.

